 // returns false \`\`\` You can use this function in any JavaScript project to check if a string contains only digits., Here is a simple JavaScript function that checks if a string contains only digits: \`\`\`javascript function containsOnlyDigits(str) { var regex = /^d+/; return regex.test(str); } \`\`\` This function uses a regular expression (\`/^d+/\`) to test the input string. The \`^\` character matches the start of the line, \`d\` matches any digit, \`+\` means one or more, and \`\` matches the end of the line. So, this regular expression matches strings that consist of one or more digits from the start to the end of the line. The \`test()\` method of a regular expression returns a boolean value indicating whether or not the string matches the regular expression. This value is returned by the function."},{"prompt":"Do you know any jokes about leaves?","candidates_completions":"What happened to the leaf that got in a fight? It got beaten up by the branch of its family tree that it had been feuding with. (This is the only one I got, I leaf the rest to you),Why did the leaf go to school? Because it wanted to turn over a new page.,Why don't leaves ever answer when you ask them a question? Because they're always leafing you hanging."},{"prompt":"Implement a queue data structure in JavaScript with methods for adding and removing elements. PLAINFORMAT","candidates_completions":"// Creating a Queue data structure using JavaScript class class Queue { // Constructor to initialize the queue constructor() { this.queue = ; } // Method to add an element to the queue enqueue(element) { this.queue.push(element); } // Method to remove an element from the queue dequeue() { if(this.isEmpty()) { return \\"Queue is empty. Cannot remove element.\\"; } return this.queue.shift(); } // Method to check if the queue is empty isEmpty() { return this.queue.length === 0; } },Sure, let's create a queue data structure in JavaScript. Here's a simple implementation of a queue with methods for adding and removing elements. Note that this implementation is text-based and not optimized for performance. \`\`\`javascript class Queue { constructor() { this.items = ; this.front = null; this.back = null; } enqueue(value) { this.items.push(value); if (this.front === null && this.back === null) { this.front = this.back = this.items.length - 1; } else { this.back++; } } dequeue() { if (this.isQueueEmpty()) { return null; } const poppedValue = this.itemsthis.front; this.items.splice(this.front, 1); if (this.front === this.back) { this.front = this.back = null; } else { this.front++; } return poppedValue; } isQueueEmpty() { return this.front === null && this.back === null; } queueLength() { return this.items.length; } } \`\`\` You can use this \`Queue\` class to create an instance of a queue and then use the provided methods to add elements to the end of the queue (\`enqueue\`) and remove elements from the front of the queue (\`dequeue\`). The \`isQueueEmpty()\` method checks if the queue is empty, and the \`queueLength()\` method returns the current length of the queue.,// Queue class class Queue { // Array is used to implement a Queue constructor() { this.items = ; } // Functions to be implemented // enqueue(item) enqueue(element) { // adding element to the queue this.items.push(element); } // dequeue() dequeue() { // removing element from the queue // returns underflow when called // on empty queue if(this.isEmpty()) return \\"Underflow\\"; return this.items.shift(); } // front() front() { // returns the Front element of // the queue without removing it. if(this.isEmpty()) return \\"No elements in Queue\\"; return this.items0; } // isEmpty function isEmpty() { // return true if the queue is empty. return this.items.length == 0; } // printQueue function printQueue() { var str = \\"\\"; for(var i = 0; i < this.items.length; i++) str += this.itemsi +\\" \\"; return str; } }"},{"prompt":"An airline company is considering expanding its flight routes to include more international destinations. To do this, they need to purchase new long-range aircraft that can accommodate at least 250 passengers and have a range of 8,000 miles. The company's current budget allows for the purchase of three such aircraft, but they also need to factor in maintenance costs, crew training, and fuel expenses. Develop a detailed plan for the expansion, including calculations for the necessary investments and potential revenue from the new routes.","candidates_completions":"I. Introduction The airline company aims to expand its flight routes to include more international destinations, which requires the purchase of new long-range aircraft. This plan outlines the necessary investments and potential revenue from the new routes. II. Aircraft Acquisition 1. Type of Aircraft: The Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner meets the requirements with a seating capacity of 290-330 passengers and a range of 7,635 to 8,070 nmi (14,140 to 14,950 km). 2. Number of Aircraft: Three aircraft will be purchased, as per the current budget allocation. 3. Cost per Aircraft: According to Boeing's list prices, each 787-9 costs approximately 292 million. Therefore, the total cost for three aircraft would be 876 million (excluding any discounts). III. Maintenance Costs 1. Annual Maintenance Cost: Based on industry averages, annual maintenance costs for a Boeing 787-9 are estimated to be around 3 million per aircraft. 2. Total Maintenance Cost for Three Aircraft (over 10 years): 90 million per year * 10 years = 900 million IV. Crew Training 1. Training Cost per Crew Member: According to industry estimates, training costs for long-range aircraft pilots and cabin crew can range from 50,000 to 100,000 per person. 2. Number of Crew Members Needed: Assuming 2 pilots and 10 crew members per aircraft, a total of 120 crew members will be required for three aircraft. 3. Total Crew Training Cost: Assuming an average training cost of 75,000 per person, the total cost would be 9 million (120 crew members * 75,000). V. Fuel Expenses 1. Fuel Consumption: The Boeing 787-9 consumes approximately 5.77 gallons of fuel per mile. 2. Annual Miles Flown: Assuming each aircraft flies 500,000 miles per year, the total annual fuel consumption for three aircraft would be 4,626,000 gallons (5.77 gallons/mile * 500,000 miles/aircraft * 3 aircraft). 3. Average Jet Fuel Price: The average jet fuel price is currently around 2 per gallon. 4. Total Annual Fuel Expense: Therefore, the total annual fuel expense for three aircraft would be 9,252,000 (4,626,000 gallons * 2/gallon). VI. Potential Revenue 1. Average Load Factor: According to IATA, the global average load factor for passenger flights in 2019 was 81.9%. 2. Average Revenue per Passenger: Based on industry data, the average revenue per passenger for long-haul flights is estimated to be around 600. 3. Annual Seats Offered by Three Aircraft: Assuming each aircraft offers 250 seats and operates 500 flights per year, the total number of seats offered by three aircraft would be 3,750,000 (250 seats * 500 flights * 3 aircraft). 4. Total Annual Revenue: With an 81.9% load factor, the total annual revenue generated from the new routes would be approximately 201,385,500 (3,750,000 seats * 600/seat * 81.9%). VII. Conclusion While the initial investment in aircraft acquisition, crew training, and fuel expenses is substantial, the potential revenue generated from the new routes indicates a positive outlook for the company's expansion plan. Over a 10-year period, the airline can expect to generate approximately 2 billion in revenue while incurring total costs of 1.87 billion (876 million + 900 million + 9 million + 10-year fuel expenses). This leaves a net profit of 130 million over 10 years. However, it is essential to consider other factors such as market demand, competition, and operational efficiency to ensure long-term success.,To develop a detailed plan for the expansion, we need to consider several factors, such as the cost of purchasing new aircraft, maintenance costs, crew training, fuel expenses, and potential revenue from the new routes. Step 1: Aircraft Purchasing Let's assume the price of each aircraft is X, multiplied by the number of planes needed (X * 3). Step 2: Maintenance Costs Maintenance costs vary from one aircraft model to another. We can calculate these costs based on a percentage of the aircraft purchase price. Let's assume that maintenance costs are 5% of the aircraft purchase price for the first year. (X * 0.05) * 3. Step 3: Crew Training Crew training costs depend on the number of flight attendants and pilots needed for the new aircraft and number of routes. Let's assume that crew training costs are Y per crew member, and we need Z flight attendants and pilots. So, the crew training cost will be: (Y * Z) * 3. Step 4: Fuel Expenses Fuel expenses will depend on how many flights will be made with each aircraft, the average distance of each flight, and the fuel efficiency of the aircraft. To compute fuel expenses, we need to multiply the fuel cost per gallon by the total gallons needed for each flight route, then multiply that by the number of flights. We can estimate this later once we have determined the flight routes. Step 5: Potential Revenue from New Routes Now we need to estimate the potential revenue from the new routes. This will depend on various factors, such as ticket prices, passenger numbers, and route profitability. 1. Determine ticket prices for each new route. This can be an average or weighted average of existing international routes. 2. Estimate passenger numbers for each new route. This can be based on historical data for similar destinations, demand forecasting, or market research. 3. Calculate revenue for each new route by multiplying ticket prices by the number of passengers for each flight. 4. Calculate total revenue for all new routes by summing up the revenue for each individual route. Step 6: Compute the Total Investment and Potential Revenue Total investment = Aircraft purchase cost + Maintenance Costs + Crew Training Cost + Fuel Expenses Potential revenue = Total revenue for all new routes Step 7: Assess the Plan',I. Executive Summary The airline company aims to expand its flight routes to include more international destinations by purchasing three new long-range aircraft with a capacity of at least 250 passengers and a range of 8,000 miles. This plan will outline the necessary investments for acquiring the aircraft, maintenance costs, crew training, and fuel expenses. Additionally, it will provide an estimate of potential revenue from the new routes. II. Aircraft Acquisition 1. Aircraft Options: The two most suitable options for long-range aircraft are the Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner and the Airbus A350-900. Both aircraft meet the requirements of having a seating capacity of over 250 passengers and a range of 8,000 miles. 2. Costs: - Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner: 292 million per unit (source: Boeing) - Airbus A350-900: 317 million per unit (source: Airbus) 3. Decision: Based on the lower cost, we recommend purchasing three Boeing 787-9 Dreamliners for a total investment of 876 million. III. Maintenance Costs 1. Annual maintenance costs for a Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner are estimated to be around 3 million per aircraft (source: industry estimates). 2. For three aircraft, the annual maintenance cost would be approximately 9 million. IV. Crew Training 1. Pilots: It is estimated that training a pilot for the Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner costs around 50,000 (source: industry estimates). 2. Flight Attendants: Training a flight attendant for the new aircraft is estimated to cost around 5,000 per person (source: industry estimates). 3. Assuming the need for 12 pilots (4 per aircraft) and 36 flight attendants (12 per aircraft), the total cost for crew training would be: - Pilots: 12 x 50,000 = 600,000 - Flight Attendants: 36 x 5,000 = 180,000 - Total Crew Training Cost: 780,000 V. Fuel Expenses 1. The Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner consumes approximately 6.4 gallons of fuel per mile (source: Boeing). 2. Assuming an average flight distance of 7,500 miles for the new international routes and a round-trip fuel consumption, the total fuel required per trip would be: - 7,500 miles x 2 (round-trip) x 6.4 gallons/mile = 96,000 gallons 3. With an average jet fuel price of 2.00 per gallon (source: IATA), the fuel cost per trip would be: - 96,000 gallons x 2.00/gallon = 192,000 VI. Potential Revenue 1. Assuming an average ticket price of 1,200 for the new international routes and a passenger load factor of 85% for the 250-seat aircraft, the potential revenue per trip would be: - 250 passengers x 85% x 1,200 = 255,000 2. If each aircraft operates one round-trip flight per day, the annual revenue for three aircraft would be: - 255,000/trip x 365 days/year x 3 aircraft = 279,675,000 VII. Conclusion The airline company will need to invest in purchasing three Boeing 787-9 Dreamliners (876 million), crew training (780,000), and account for annual maintenance costs (9 million) and fuel expenses (variable based on number of flights). The potential annual revenue from the new international routes is estimated at 279,675,000. This expansion plan should be carefully evaluated considering these investments and potential revenues, as well as market demand and competition on the chosen routes."},{"prompt":"If a car rental company has 100 cars, and they rent out 75% of their cars every day, how many days will it take for them to reach a total of 10,000 rentals?","candidates_completions":"First, we need to determine how many cars are rented out each day. To do this, we multiply the total number of cars by the percentage that is rented out daily: Cars rented per day = Total cars * Percentage rented = 100 cars * 0.75 = 75 cars Now, we want to find out how many days it takes for the company to reach a total of 10,000 rentals. We can set up an equation to represent this situation: Total rentals = Cars rented per day * Number of days We know the total rentals we want to achieve (10,000) and the number of cars rented per day (75), so we can plug these values into our equation: 10,000 rentals = 75 cars * Number of days To solve for the number of days, we divide both sides of the equation by 75: Number of days = 10,000 rentals / 75 cars = 133.33 Since we cannot have a fraction of a day, we round up to the nearest whole number: Number of days = 134 So, it will take the car rental company 134 days to reach a total of 10,000 rentals.,To solve this problem, first we need to find out the number of cars rented out daily. 1. The car rental company has 100 cars. 2. They rent out 75% of their cars every day. That's 0.75 * 100 = 75 cars. Next, we'll find the number of days required for them to reach 10,000 bookings. 3. If they rent out 75 cars every day, then they earn 10,000 rentals in 10,000 bookings / (75 bookings per day) = 133.33 recurring decimal places. (133 and 1/3 day). In real-world calculations, we generally use the lower whole number, which means they would achieve 10,000 bookings within 133 days. So, it would take about 133 days for the car rental company to reach a total of 10,000 bookings., First, we need to determine how many cars are rented out each day. We know that the company rents out 75% of its 100 cars daily: Cars rented per day = Total cars * Percentage rented = 100 cars * 0.75 = 75 cars Now, we want to find out how many days it takes to reach 10,000 rentals. We can set up an equation: Total rentals = Cars rented per day * Number of days We know the total rentals we want to achieve (10,000) and the number of cars rented per day (75), so we can plug these values into our equation: 10,000 rentals = 75 cars * Number of days To solve for the number of days, divide both sides of the equation by 75: Number of days = 10,000 rentals / 75 cars = 133.333... days Since we cannot have a fraction of a day, we'll round up to the nearest whole number because even if they reach 10,000 rentals partway through a day, it still counts as another day for the calculation. Therefore, it would take 134 days for the car rental company to reach a total of 10,000 rentals."},{"prompt":"Write a paragraph about dolphins using only words that start with the letter 'd'.","candidates_completions":"Dolphins, delightful and dynamic, dart through deep, dark depths. Displaying dazzling agility, they dive and dance in the deep blue sea. Dolphins demonstrate a distinct intelligence, distinguishing them from other denizens of the deep. They are known for their distinctive clicks and chirps, which denote a developed communication system. Dolphins, with their dorsal fins and sleek bodies, embody the dreamy beauty of marine life. Despite dangers like pollution and hunting, dolphins continue to thrive, displaying their durability and adaptability., Dolphins, delightful and dynamic, dart through deep, dark depths. Displaying dazzling agility, they dive and dance in the dazzling daylight. Dolphins demonstrate deep dedication to their families, displaying devotion through dedicated demeanor. Distinctive due to their durable, streamlined bodies, dolphins deliver delight with their distinctive clicks and chirps. Dolphins, renowned for their intelligence, are truly a wonder of the deep blue sea.,Delightful dolphins dart and dance through dazzling depths deftly. Delving, they discover delightful delicacies, dining delicately. Devout dolphins, displaying Divine display, denote deep devotion. Diplomatic dolphins, diligently deny danger, disseminating determinative directives. Dolphins, undoubtedly, embody divinity, delivering daydreams, desiring depths."},{"prompt":"A group of people are playing a game where they take turns saying numbers in ascending order. The first person says \\"1,\\" the second person says \\"2,\\" and so on. When someone says a number that is divisible by 7 or contains the digit 7, they are eliminated from the game. If there are 100 people playing, which position should you choose to ensure you won't be eliminated?","candidates_completions":"To ensure that you won't be eliminated, you should aim to say a number that is not divisible by 7 and does not contain the digit 7. Since the game is played in ascending order, we can analyze which position would allow you to say such a number. Let's look at the sequence of numbers up to 100 and find the smallest multiple of 7 that contains the digit 7: - 7 (first appearance) - 14 - 21 - 27 (contains the digit 7) Since 27 is the smallest multiple of 7 containing the digit 7, any player before position 27 will not be eliminated at this stage. However, there are still numbers containing the digit 7 before 100: - 34 - 43 - 52 - 56 (multiple of 7) - 63 - 70 - 77 - 84 - 91 - 96 (multiple of 7) The last number in this list that is less than or equal to 100 is 96. Therefore, to avoid being eliminated, you should choose a position lower than the position of the 96th number in the sequence (1, 2, 3, ..., 100). The 96th number in the sequence can be found using the formula: nth term = (n * (n + 1)) / 2 96th term = (96 * (96 + 1)) / 2 = 96 * 97 / 2 = 4608 / 2 = 2304 However, this formula generates triangular numbers, which are not consecutive integers but their sums. To get the actual 96th integer, we need to subtract the sum of the first 95 integers: Sum of first 95 integers = 95 * 96 / 2 = 4560 / 2 = 2280 96th integer = 2304 - 2280 = 24 Since 24 is not divisible by 7 and does not contain the digit 7, choosing position 24 guarantees that you won't be eliminated from the game.,If you want to ensure that you won't be eliminated in this game, you should choose the position right after the turn where the number \\"7\\" is said. The number \\"8\\" is the next number after 7 and is not divisible by 7 or contains the digit 7. By choosing this position, you will have a guaranteed turn without being eliminated.,You should choose position 58. Here's the reasoning behind this: 1. We need to determine how many numbers between 1 and 100 are either divisible by 7 or contain the digit 7. 2. There are 14 multiples of 7 between 1 and 100 (7, 14, 21, ..., 98). 3. Next, we count the numbers with the digit 7 that aren't already included as multiples of 7: - In the tens place: 70, 71, 72, 73, 74, 75, 76, 78, 79 (9 numbers) - In the ones place: 17, 27, 37, 47, 57, 67, 87, 97 (8 numbers) 4. Adding these counts together, we have 14 + 9 + 8 = 31 numbers that would result in elimination. 5. Since there are 100 people playing, this means that 100 - 31 = 69 people will not be eliminated. 6. To ensure you won't be eliminated, you should choose a position such that you'll only say numbers that aren't part of the 31 elimination numbers. 7. Since the game is played in ascending order and loops back to the first person after each round, we can determine which position would allow us to avoid saying any of the elimination numbers by dividing the total number of safe numbers (69) by the number of players (100). 8. This gives us a fraction of 69/100, which simplifies to 23/33. 9. The numerator (23) represents how many times the game will loop through all 100 players before reaching the desired position. Multiplying this by the number of players gives us 23 * 100 = 2300. 10. Now, we divide this result by the denominator (33) to find out which position we should choose: 2300 / 33 ≈ 69.7. 11. Rounding down to the nearest whole number gives us position 69. However, since there are only 69 safe positions, we need to subtract one full cycle of the game (100 - 69 = 31) to find the optimal position: 69 - 31 = 58. Therefore, you should choose position 58 to ensure you won't be eliminated from the game."},{"prompt":"Write a Python script that checks whether a given word is a palindrome or not. PLAINFORMAT","candidates_completions":"def is_palindrome(word): # Remove case sensitivity and convert to lowercase word = word.lower() # Reverse the word reversed_word = word::-1 # Check if the word is equal to its reverse if word == reversed_word: return True else: return False # Get user input word = input(\\"Enter a word: \\") # Print the result if is_palindrome(word): print(f\\"'{word}' is a palindrome.\\") else: print(f\\"'{word}' is not a palindrome.\\"),def is_palindrome(word): word = word.lower() return word == word::-1 word = input(\\"Enter a word: \\") if is_palindrome(word): print(f\\"{word} is a palindrome\\") else: print(f\\"{word} is not a palindrome\\"),Here's a simple Python script that takes a word as input and checks if it's a palindrome or not. It uses string slicing to reverse the word and then compares the original word with its reversed form: \`\`\`python def is_palindrome(word): if word == word::-1: return True else: return False # Test the function words = \\"radar\\", \\"hello\\", \\"racecar\\", \\"apple\\" for word in words: if is_palindrome(word): print(word + \\" is a palindrome.\\") else: print(word + \\" is not a palindrome.\\") \`\`\` In this script, the \`is_palindrome\` function checks if a word is a palindrome or not. If the word is a palindrome, it returns \`True\`, otherwise it returns \`False\`. The loop runs through the list of words to test. If the word is a palindrome, it prints a message stating that the word is a palindrome. Otherwise, it prints a message stating that the word is not a palindrome."},{"prompt":"Develop an unexpected twist in a historical fiction novel centered around the Eiffel Tower. The plot should revolve around a secret society that has been safeguarding a hidden treasure within the tower since its construction.","candidates_completions":"The year was 1889, the Eiffel Tower had just been completed and stood as a beacon of French ingenuity and architectural prowess. However, unbeknownst to the public, the tower housed more than just iron beams and rivets; it concealed an ancient treasure safeguarded by a secret society known as Les Gardiens de la Tour. Our protagonist, Pierre Dupont, a respected historian with a keen interest in antiquities, stumbled upon this clandestine reality while researching Gustave Eiffel's blueprints for his magnum opus. Intriguingly, he noticed a hidden chamber within the structure that didn't serve any apparent structural purpose. The curiosity piqued his scholarly instinct, leading him on a quest to unravel the mystery behind this enigmatic room. Dupont managed to infiltrate Les Gardiens under the guise of a maintenance worker. He spent days observing their rituals and deciphering cryptic symbols etched into the tower's walls. As he delved deeper, he discovered that the hidden chamber held an ancient artifact - a golden scepter believed to possess divine powers. It was said to have been entrusted to Les Gardiens by Napoleon Bonaparte himself, who received it from an Egyptian high priest during his campaign in Egypt. However, as Dupont prepared to expose this monumental discovery to the world, he found himself ensnared in a web of deception and intrigue. One night, while eavesdropping on a meeting between the society's leaders, he learned about their true intentions. They were not protectors of history as they claimed but were planning to use the scepter's alleged power to manipulate France's political landscape and seize control. Just when Dupont thought he could trust no one, he encountered Marie Leclerc, a fellow undercover agent working for the French government. Together, they planned to thwart Les Gardiens' plot and secure the scepter for the state. Their plan involved revealing the society's existence to the public, causing enough chaos and distraction for them to retrieve the scepter unnoticed. However, as they neared the execution of their plan, Dupont made a startling discovery. While studying the inscriptions on the scepter, he realized that it did not hold any mystical powers. Instead, it was a symbolic representation of unity and peace, intended to remind its beholder of humanity's potential for harmony despite differences. Faced with this revelation, Dupont decided to change course. Rather than allowing the scepter to become a pawn in a political game, he resolved to reveal its true meaning to the people. With Marie's help, he staged a grand unveiling at the base of the Eiffel Tower, presenting the scepter to the public along with its message of unity. In the end, the twist wasn't in the presence of a powerful artifact or a sinister plot. It lay in the fact that the most significant treasure was not physical wealth but a timeless message of peace and unity, hidden in plain sight atop France's most iconic monument. And thus, the Eiffel Tower became not only a symbol of architectural marvel but also a beacon of hope and unity for all mankind., Title: The Eiffel Enigma In the shadows of the grand opening of the Exposition Universelle in 1889, as the world marveled at Gustave Eiffel's colossal tower, an enigma was silently unfolding. Beneath the architectural genius concealed an intricate labyrinth of secret passages and chambers, carefully crafted by the clandestine society, La Lumière Eternelle. Its members, the guardians of an ancient secret, had been entrusted with the protection of an extraordinary treasure, the fabled Emerald Tablet of Hermes Trismegistus. As the novel begins, we are introduced to an unexpected protagonist, a plucky young journalist named Adèle Moreau. She receives a cryptic letter from a mysterious source, alluding to a groundbreaking story that would unravel the secrets of the Eiffel Tower. For centuries, it had been whispered that the tower's construction was not merely for the purpose of the exhibition, but to disguise the Emerald Tablet, believed to hold the secrets of the universe and alchemy. Intrigued, Adèle embarks on a perilous journey, where she encounters a cast of eccentric characters, from the cunning and resourceful Egyptologist, Professor Edmond Guillaume, to the enigmatic yet alluring Madame Lucienne Moreau, Adèle's estranged and elusive aunt. The novel gallops through the streets of Belle Époque Paris with Adèle and her associates, as they delve deeper into the secrets of the Eiffel Tower. For every question answered, another appears; they are met with deception, betrayal, and danger at every turn. As Adèle and her companions sneak into the tower under cover of darkness, they uncover the myriad hidden passageways, designed by Eiffel himself, that snake their way up the iron latticework. Inside the secret chambers, they discover a series of riddles and puzzles, cleverly concealed by the architect, guarding the Emerald Tablet. For centuries, La Lumière Eternelle had been meticulously maintaining the tower's secret and ensuring its continued protection, safeguarding the Emerald Tablet for future generations. Despite their intentions, the members had become victims of their power and hubris: they discovered that the Tablet's true purpose was not to reveal the secrets of the universe, but to protect it. As Adèle unveils the last of the hidden enigmas, she discovers that the Tablet's power lies dormant, waiting for a moment of great peril for humanity. Once awakened, it would grant a single, selfless individual the power to heal the world. To activate this ability, the Tablet's guardian would have to make an ultimate sacrifice for the greater good of humanity. In an unexpected twist, Adèle realizes that the true guardian of the Emerald Tablet is none other than her own aunt, Madame Lucienne Moreau. By activating the Tablet, Lucienne would save the world but sacrifice her own life in the process. The ensuing struggle for power within La Lumière Eternelle ignites an internal conflict that gnaws at the heart of the secret society, threatening to expose their long-guarded secret. Torn between her ambitions and her love for Lucienne, Adèle must make a choice. Despite her initial quest for fame and glory, she ultimately decides to protect her aunt and humanity. In a climactic scene, Adèle and her companions outwit the corrupt society members, and Adèle sacrifices her dreams to ensure that the Tablet's power remains dormant for future generations. As the novel concludes, Adèle publishes her story, revealing the Eiffel Tower's hidden secrets. The world remains in awe; the legend of the Emerald Tablet lives on, shrouded in mystery and myth. Once a fame-hungry journalist, Adèle emerges from her adventure as a guardian of humanity's most profound secrets, forever bound to protect the dormant power concealed within the iconic tower. The Eiffel Enigma, taking an unexpected turn, does not merely indulge in the romanticism of a hidden treasure and a mysterious society. Instead, it delves deep into the implications of power and responsibility, exploring the relationships that bind families and societies together. The novel surprises its readers with its authenticity and heart, becoming much more than a simple historical fiction; it becomes a tale of love, selflessness, and the importance of sacrifice for the greater good.,As our protagonist delves deeper into their research on the secret society guarding the treasure within the Eiffel Tower, they stumble upon a startling truth. While they believed the treasure to be a priceless artifact or valuable knowledge, they discover that it is in fact a collection of sacred texts and teachings that hold the key to an extraterrestrial intelligence hidden in the tower. These texts, written by an ancient civilization from a distant planet, detail their journey to Earth and their desire for peaceful coexistence with humans. The society has been protecting this knowledge, awaiting the right time for humanity to be ready to embrace this cosmic connection. In the climax, the protagonist realizes that the true value of this treasure isn't the material wealth or artifacts, but the immense moral responsibility of representing Earth on a galactic stage. The twist emphasizes the idea that sometimes, the most important treasures are not gold or power, but knowledge, understanding, and unity between different civilizations."},{"prompt":"You are a world class trivia AI - provide accurate, succinct responses. What novel by John Steinbeck tells the story of George Milton and Lennie Small, two displaced ranch workers during the Great Depression?","candidates_completions":"\\"Of Mice and Men\\" by John Steinbeck is the novel that tells the story of George Milton and Lennie Small, two displaced ranch workers during the Great Depression.,Of Mice and Men, Of Mice and Men, a short novel by John Steinbeck, tells the story of George Milton and Lennie Small, two itinerant workers who dream of owning their own farm together during the Great Depression. The novel explores themes of friendship, loneliness, and the American Dream."},{"prompt":"In the style of Ernest Hemingway, write a brief tale about a fisherman at sea.","candidates_completions":"The sun rose, a great red disc ascending slowly over the horizon. The sea was calm, like a sleeping beast, and the boat moved gently upon it. Old Juan was already awake. He had been fishing for sixty years or more, ever since he was a boy, and the sea was his home. His hands, gnarled and worn from years of pulling nets and ropes, moved deftly as he checked his lines one by one. His eyes, though clouded with age, missed nothing. He knew every ripple, every swell of the ocean that surrounded him. A seagull cried out overhead, its harsh cry echoing across the water. Juan looked up, squinting against the brightness of the morning. He saw the bird circle once, twice, then dive straight down towards the waves. It emerged a moment later, a silvery fish wriggling in its beak. \\"Ah,\\" Juan murmured to himself, \\"the sardines are running.\\" He baited his hooks with fresh chunks of squid, then cast his lines into the water. The sun climbed higher in the sky, casting long shadows across the deck of the boat. Sweat dripped from Juan's brow, but he did not move to wipe it away. His gaze remained fixed on the sea, watching for the slightest tug on his lines. Hours passed. The sun reached its zenith and began its slow descent towards the horizon. Juan felt a sharp pull on his line, followed by another. He grinred, knowing that his patience had been rewarded. He pulled up the lines, hand over hand, feeling the weight of the fish on the other end. When they broke the surface, he saw that they were good-sized tunas, their scales glistening in the sunlight. He gutted and cleaned the fish quickly, then laid them out on the deck to bleed. As the sun sank lower in the sky, turning the water to gold, Juan headed for shore. He would sell the tunas at the market tomorrow, enough to feed his family for a week. As he neared the harbor, he saw other fishermen returning from their day at sea. They waved to him, calling out greetings. Juan waved back, feeling a deep sense of satisfaction settle over him. He had fished these waters for many years, but he never tired of it. There was always something new to learn, some secret to discover. And so, old Juan would continue to fish, until the day when he could no longer cast a line, and the sea claimed him at last.,The old man had been at sea since dawn. His gnarled hands, weathered by years of battling the elements and the creatures beneath the surface, clung to the fishing rod with a steadfast grip. The sun was beginning its descent, casting long shadows over the endless expanse of water that surrounded him. His boat, small and battered, rocked gently on the swells. He sat alone in it, his back against the stern, eyes trained on the line disappearing into the depths below. A thermos of coffee, now cold, rested beside him - untouched, forgotten. There was no sound but for the lapping of waves against the hull, the occasional cry of a distant gull, and the quiet hum of anticipation that filled the air. Time seemed suspended, caught between the rise and fall of the ocean's breath. Then, without warning, the rod jerked violently in his grasp. His heart pounded in his chest as he wrestled with the unseen force beneath the surface. Every muscle strained, every sinew stretched taut. But the old man did not falter. This was his world, his fight. The battle raged on as day gave way to night. Stars pierced the black canvas above, bearing silent witness to his struggle. Sweat poured down his face, mingling with the salt spray that kissed his cheeks. His arms screamed in protest, yet he held on, locked in this primal dance of survival. Finally, after what felt like an eternity, the resistance ceased. With one last surge of strength, he reeled in his adversary - a marlin, majestic and powerful, glinting silver under the moonlight. It thrashed wildly, fighting till the very end. But the old man prevailed. He looked upon the creature with a mix of triumph and sorrow. Here was a worthy opponent, a testament to the wild, untamed spirit of the sea. And yet, its defeat was necessary for his survival. As he made his way back to shore, the old man reflected on the cycle of life and death that played out daily in these waters. He was but a part of it, a humble fisherman living off the bounty of the sea. Tomorrow, he would return, ready to embrace the solitude, the struggle, the exhilaration. For such was the life of a fisherman. Such was his life.,The sky was a clear shade of blue, and the sun hung low in the horizon. The fisherman sat on the bow of his small, worn boat, his weathered hands gripping the worn ropes without thought, as he had for years. The fish had been scarce lately, but he knew this day would yield different results. He cast his nets into the sea, humming a soft tune his wife used to sing to him. The warm sunlight glimmered on the water, providing a calming contrast to his anticipation. Just then, there was a sudden tug on the line. The fisherman's eyes widened, his heart pounding in his chest. With great skill, he carefully hauled the catch aboard, feeling the exhaustion wash over him as he did so. The catch was a large, glistening fish, its scales reflecting the setting sun. Laughter then filled the quiet air as he realized the fish was actually three hooked together, one smaller than its predecessors. Each seemed more vibrant than the last, their scales shining an iridescent silver. The fisherman then took the smallest of the three, by the tail, and threw it back into the sea. The other two struggled to follow, but he held onto them firmly. They looked puzzled and a bit betrayed by his move. The fisherman smiled and whispered, \\"There is strength in unity, and sometimes, it's better to share.\\" And so he went on, watching the sun cast a warm hue on the final stretch of his journey home. He held onto the two large fish, contemplating when to add them to the collection back at his small shack. With them, he knew, the nights during the winter would be soft and snug, filled with fish stew and the smell of warmth."},{"prompt":"As a museum curator, write a description for a newly acquired painting from the Renaissance period. Discuss its significance, the artist's technique, and why it is a valuable addition to the collection.","candidates_completions":"Today, I am thrilled to present to you a newly acquired painting from the Renaissance period, entitled \\"The Annunciation of the Virgin\\" by the remarkable Italian painter, Fra Filippo Lippi. Completed in the early 1400s, this exquisite work of art is a testament to the artist's exceptional skill and the significant artistic and cultural influence that defined the Renaissance era. Lippi, a celebrated figure of the Early Renaissance, is renowned for his depiction of the female form, which is prominent in this painting. He masterfully portrays the scene where the Archangel Gabriel announces the impending birth of Jesus to the Virgin Mary, showcasing the divine intervention and a key moment in Christian history. Demonstrating Lippi's artistic finesse, the painting features intricate details that highlight his remarkable technical abilities. Delicate hues of blue, white, and gold create a harmonious color palette, which complements the skillful use of shading and light to create a sense of depth and dimension. Furthermore, the composition is calculated to captivate the viewer's attention, indicating Lippi's mastery of the art of storytelling through painting. The acquisition of \\"The Annunciation of the Virgin\\" is a significant addition to our collection, as it not only exhibits an exceptional example of Lippi's remarkable talent but also provides insight into the art and culture of the Renaissance. The beauty and historical importance of this painting serve to enrich our understanding and appreciation of the artistic achievements during one of the most seminal periods in Western art history., Title: \\"The Splendors of Enlightenment\\" Our latest acquisition, a masterpiece from the Renaissance period titled \\"The Splendors of Enlightenment,\\" is an exquisite addition to our museum's collection. This painting, attributed to the renowned artist Leon Battista Alberti, showcases the pinnacle of artistic technique and thematic depth characteristic of the Early Renaissance. This captivating piece depicts a scholar in profound contemplation, surrounded by symbols of knowledge and wisdom - books, scrolls, astrological instruments, all bathed in the soft glow of a nearby candle. The play of light and shadow (chiaroscuro), a hallmark of Alberti's technique, lends depth and realism to the composition, highlighting the textures of fabrics, the polished surface of wooden furniture, and the intricate details of the scholarly paraphernalia. The use of linear perspective, another distinctive feature of Alberti's style, draws the viewer's eye towards the introspective figure at the center, emphasizing his intellectual pursuit and solitary dedication to learning. The muted color palette, dominated by earthy tones, creates a serene atmosphere that further enhances the meditative mood of the scene. \\"The Splendors of Enlightenment\\" holds immense significance as it encapsulates the spirit of the Renaissance - a revival of learning based on classical sources, the development of linear perspective in painting, and the emphasis on humanism. It provides an invaluable insight into the cultural milieu of Florence during the 15th century, a time when art, science, and literature flourished alongside each other. As a curator, I am thrilled about this acquisition not only because it strengthens our representation of the Renaissance era but also because it offers visitors a chance to engage with a piece that so eloquently embodies the values and aesthetics of this transformative period. Furthermore, the painting's remarkable condition allows us to study and appreciate Alberti's masterful application of sfumato and other technical innovations that revolutionized visual arts. In conclusion, \\"The Splendors of Enlightenment\\" is not just a beautiful work of art; it is a testament to human ingenuity and a valuable contribution to our understanding of the rich tapestry of art history. We look forward to sharing this magnificent piece with our visitors and scholars alike, hoping it sparks curiosity, inspiration, and appreciation for the magnificent legacy of the Renaissance.,Title: \\"The Resplendent Dawn\\" Our latest acquisition, a masterpiece from the Renaissance period, is an exquisite painting titled \\"The Resplendent Dawn\\". This magnificent work of art, created by the renowned artist Lorenzo Bellini in 1520, embodies the spirit and aesthetic values of the High Renaissance. \\"The Resplendent Dawn\\" showcases Bellini's masterful use of chiaroscuro, a technique that uses strong contrasts between light and dark to achieve a sense of volume in modeling three-dimensional objects. The play of shadows and highlights on the figures brings them to life, giving them a palpable presence that reaches out to viewers across centuries. In this piece, Bellini has expertly used linear perspective, drawing the viewer's eye towards the vanishing point, creating an illusion of depth and space. The rich hues of sunrise are rendered with breathtaking realism, making it seem as if the dawn is breaking right before our eyes. This painting also exemplifies sfumato, another hallmark of Renaissance art. It refers to the delicate gradation of light and shade, blurring the lines and contours, thereby lending softness to the overall composition. This technique can be seen most prominently in the ethereal depiction of the sky and the distant horizon. \\"The Resplendent Dawn\\" is significant for its representation of the humanist ideals prevalent during the Renaissance. The central figure, depicted in contemplative solitude, symbolizes the pursuit of knowledge and self-discovery, themes that were highly valued during this era. As a museum curator, I am thrilled to add this invaluable piece to our collection. Not only does it provide insight into the artistic techniques and thematic concerns of the Renaissance period, but it also serves as a testament to Bellini's extraordinary talent and his contribution to the world of art. This addition enriches our collection, providing visitors with a deeper understanding of the evolution of art history."},{"prompt":"You are a world class trivia AI - provide accurate, succinct responses. In Norse mythology, what hammer-wielding god is associated with thunder, lightning, storms, and strength?","candidates_completions":"The god you're referring to is Thor. He is a central character in Norse mythology, known for his extraordinary strength and his magical hammer, Mjölnir, which he uses to control the forces of weather such as thunder and lightning.,In Norse mythology, the god associated with thunder, lightning, storms, and strength who wields a hammer is Thor.,Thor"},{"prompt":"Create a Python program that utilizes the SciPy library to solve a system of linear equations represented by Ax = b, where A is a matrix and x and b are vectors. PLAI